verbose_text: Methylmalonic acidemia (MMA), an autosomal recessive genetic disease, which affects organic acid metabolism, is mainly caused by a defective methylmalonyl-CoA mutase or abnormal metabolism of coenzyme cobalamin (Vitamin B 12) (Deodato, Boenzi, Santorelli, & Dionisi-Vici, 2006; Oberholzer, Levin, Burgess, & Young, 1967).
evidence: MMA), an autosomal recessive genetic disease, which affects organic acid metabolism, is mainly caused by a defective methylmalonyl-CoA mutase
